subSubSection.paragraph:
This new species is similar to
H. qingliangensis
Tang, Belokobylskij, He & Chen, 2013 from China (Zhejiang Province), but differs from the later by having the first flagellar segment 1.1 x longer than second segment (0.9 x in
H. qingliangensis
), mesoscutum almost entirely coriaceous and with rather dense setae arranged widely along notauli (almost smooth and with very sparse setae along notauli in
H. qingliangensis
), hind femur 3.6 x longer than wide (4.2-4.4 x in
H. qingliangensis
), suture between second and third metasomal tergites distinctly sinuate (almost straight in
H. qingliangensis
), median length of second metasomal tergite 0.45 x its basal width (0.6 x in
H. qingliangensis
), ovipositor sheath 0.6-0.8 x as long as metasoma and 0.50-0.55 as long as fore wing (1.4 and 0.85 x respectively in
H. qingliangensis
).

Also the new species is similar to
H. weolchulsanus
sp. nov., but differs from it in having the head behind eyes (dorsal view) distinctly roundly narrowed (weakly narrowed in
H. weolchulsanus
), length of first tergite equal to its apical width. (0.85 x in
H. weolchulsanus
), suture between second and third metasomal tergites distinctly sinuate (very weakly sinuate in
H. weolchulsanus
), ovipositor sheath longer, 0.6-0.8 x as long as metasoma and 0.50-0.55 as long as fore wing (shorter, 0.3 x as long as metasoma and 0.2 x as long as fore wing in
H. weolchulsanus
) and pterostigma entirely brown (light brown in
H. weolchulsanus
).
